Publicis’s Levy Says COO Naouri Could Win CEO Post, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-30T23:48:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/publicis-s-levy-says-coo-naouri-could-win-ceo-post-ft-reports.html
Publicis Group SA Chief Executive
Officer  Maurice Levy  has indicated that Chief Operating Officer
Jean-Yves Naouri, who has also been appointed executive chairman
of the company’s Publicis Worldwide unit, is most likely to
succeed him, the Financial Times reported, citing an interview.  Naouri is “clearly in a leading position for winning the
race” to become the company’s next CEO when Levy stands down in
“a few more years,” Levy said, according to the FT. “This is
part of the  succession plan ,” Levy said, the FT reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 